name: Vision Essentials by Kaiser Permanente
comment: As far as I can tell all bathrooms in the Oakland Kaiser hospitals are now "all genders"

name: Sacred Money Studios/Prosperity Pie Shoppe
comment: Have to be a paying customer as far as I know.

name: Birch coffee
directions: Left  back corner
comment: Diverse & friendly staff!

name: Berkeley Bowl
directions: Right side of the store behind the cafe.
comment: Restrooms are neither single stall nor gender neutral. However, this is one of the safest businesses to be in. You're extremely unlikely to be harassed or questioned. Also, no one will question whether you're a paying customer.

name: Burger tap & shake
directions: Straight back on the left hand side
comment: Just ask for the code... currently it is 12344

name: La Prima Tazza
directions: In the back on the left
comment: For paying customers but baristas are kind and likely wouldn't stop you

name: Lonestar College-CyFair
directions: Technology Building, second floor.
comment: the bathrooms facing the lake are the quietest. If you don't feel safe, look for the faculty offices with signs on their doors for support.

name: The Black Cow Coffee Co.
directions: The wall opposite the door you enter through.

name: Pie Five
directions: Walk in just head straight forward
comment: Both male and female single stall bathrooms, don't have to be a paying customer. This place also has a Coca-Cola freestyle machine so that's cool.

name: The Whip
directions: Right in front of the doors.
comment: It's a restaurant so probably only for customers but they are very chill hipster types.

name: Matheson Memorial Library
directions: Family restroom at the back of the children's area on the ground floor. (adults are welcome to use it)

name: Cal State LA Student Union
directions: Second floor
comment: They are labeled as gender neutral (:

name: Broadway Dance Center
directions: Sibgle bathroom, 2nd floor by studio B
comment: Sometimes accessible, but elevator is not reliable.

name: bfresh
directions: Straight back through the store when you walk in

name: Sawyer Library, Williams College
directions: When you enter the building, you're on level 3. Take elevator (in the back of the building) or stairs up to level 5. Bathroom is near elevator.
comment: This is a Williams College building but it is open to the public 8-5:00 nearly every day, and as late as 2:00am weekdays during the school year.

name: Thomas Crane Public Library
directions: Second floor near reference desk
comment: Free and open to all. Single use, gender neutral and accessible.

name: The Highwire Lounge
directions: In the back of the bar to the left.

name: Changing Perceptions
directions: Through the corridor, past the sofa area, up the steps and to the left
comment: Browse the furniture for a bit and you're good to go

name: Beasley's Chicken + Honey
directions: All the way in the back of the restaurant.
comment: Most likely for paying customers.

name: Colorado State University-LSC
directions:
100 Level-south of the Ramskellar 
200 Level-outside of the southwest corner of the food court
300 Level-the hallway east to the grand ballrooms

name: Sharp Mesa Vista Hospital
directions: From the main entrance, turn right. It will immediately be on the left.

name: Toast
directions: Adjacent to the back door
comment: They'd prefer you be a customer, but they're cool (and the restrooms aren't visible from the counter)

name: Yorktown High School
directions: Far corner of the school by "Social Studies pod"
comment: Must be either Yorktown High School guest, student, or staff member.

name: Starbucks
directions: To the right if the counter

name: Ackerman Union
directions: A-level, across from the gendered restrooms.

name: The Black Drop Coffeehouse
directions: Bathrooms are in a small hall kittycorner from the entrance.
comment: You must ask for a key at the counter. Paying customers only, but the staff are trans friendly (and some trans) so if you're desperate, just explain.

name: 21 Bruin Walk, Los Angeles, CA 90095, USA
directions: First floor of Counseling and Psychology Services building.
comment: No need to have an appointment!

name: AAA Ocala
directions: Through brown door w/ restroom sign, straight back down hall last door on left.
comment: You do not have to be a member or customer to use. Bathroom is a the handicap accessible, and is a single stall gender-neutral separate from other bathrooms.

name: Front Range Community College - Larimer
directions: When entering from the front doors, walk past the information desk, turn left when the Learning Opportunity Center is on your right, the bathroom is on your right past the water bottle stations.
comment: There's a vacant/occupied knob on the door, if it's occupied then you can loiter on your phone or something just outside the door (plenty of people use it besides trans people on campus).

name: Endgame
directions: off to the left on the ground floor
comment: if busy, the cafe next door has a single, accessible unisex bathroom & they are connected during open hours

name: Sterling College
directions: All around the Sterling college campus and in the dorm buildings. As well as Dunbar Hall which is the large building on Sterling Drive. The Sterling campus buildings will be marked by a name plate that is mint green boarderd by a forest green trim and the name of the building is in white text.
comment: Likely able to use restrooms without question in big buildings but in dorm buildings you may be asked who you are. The only reason is that it is a small community and people usually know who everyone is.

name: Endgame Cafe
comment: get key from the coffee pickup area, they won't hassle you, if it's busy there's safe single-gender restrooms at Endgame nextdoor that don't even need a key

name: Pokecraft
comment: There's an entrance in the front and back, back entrance rather private usually no one sitting in hallway.

name: Immediate Medical Care
comment: You need to ask the receptionist for the key.

name: University of Rochester
directions: First floor, Lam Square multi-stall all gender restrooms, Humanities Center,  second floor three single stall all gender restrooms

name: Geelong Regional Library - Geelong branch
directions: Outside the building itself, if you're facing the entrance, they're on the left wall
comment: Often not particularly clean, but generally safe.

name: Nature's Brew
directions: Two unisex bathrooms near kitchens
comment: You need to be a paying customer, but staff is friendly

name: Ermine Vintage
directions: Behind the counter, just ask.
comment: Just ask.

name: Herkimer College
directions: Entrance to the JH building coming from the CA building

name: Rough Trade
directions: Next to the photobooth near the entrance

name: Leavey Center Georgetown University
directions: Enter the Leavey center and find your way to the elevators that bring you tothe higher levels of Leavey. On the third and fifth floors (the LGBT Center and the Center for Milticultural Equity and Access) there will be single stall gender neutral bathroom to the left of the elevators.
comment: No requirements! Staff are welcoming and accepting of all identities.

name: Candler Park Market
directions: Straight back, at the end of the first aisle.
comment: You might want to pretend to browse depending on how busy things are.

name: Verve Coffee Roasters
comment: IDK if you have to be a paying customer.

name: Kortes supermarket
directions: Ask cashier where the bathroom is, you need permission
comment: Act like you are browsing

name: Museum of the Oregon Territory
directions: To get to the unisex bathrooms, go through the "classroom area" behind the front desk and enter the hallway to the right.
comment: Talk to front desk before using restroom (just say something like "I just wanted to see what this is all about" or something, though if you have time the museum is worth checking out). Second and Third floor bathrooms are gendered stalls, but both bathrooms on first Floor are unisex. As of writing this (Feb 2017) staff are all LGBTQ+ friendly (although there is a large volunteer base which I cannot speak for).

name: Museum of the Oregon Territory
directions: To get to the unisex bathrooms, go through the "classroom area" behind the front desk and enter the hallway to the right.
comment: Talk to front desk before using restroom (just say something like "I just wanted to see what this is all about" or something, though if you have time the museum is worth checking out). Second and Third floor bathrooms are gendered stalls, but both bathrooms on first Floor are unisex. As of writing this (Feb 2017) staff are all LGBTQ+ friendly (although there is a large volunteer base which I cannot speak for).

name: Capital City Bakery
directions: Small place, so the bathroom is easy to locate when you walk in the front door.
comment: Super friendly!

name: Michael's arts and crafts
directions: Back of the stoor by employee office
comment: They allow you to use whichever bathroom you are comfortable using!

name: Target
directions: Family restroom

name: sos thrift store
directions: back left wall

name: The Good Will Social Club
directions: At the very back of the venue on the restaurant side, walk past the long tables, past the arcade and pinball machines, around the corner are several individual gender neutral washrooms.
comment: Half a dozen individual gender neutral restaurants.

name: MIAD
directions: River level floor
comment: Need to sign in with security desk as a visitor but you should be fine

name: University of Windsor Leddy Library
directions: Through the entrance, first door to your right, across from the front desk.
comment: Has a lock mechanism where you push the big red button to lock the door, **sometimes it doesn't work** so be sure to lock it manually as well.

name: Navos MHWC
directions: At least one person floor.
comment: It is a MH clinic, and staff is cool.

name: Indepenent Bar & Café
directions: In the Seminole Heights neighborhood of Tampa.
comment: If you needed to go, they'd welcome you.

name: Woods Coffee
directions: Outside entrances to multiple gender neutral bathrooms.
comment: Open to the public, may be a bit dirty but it's safe.

name: Sightglass Coffee
directions: To the right of the coffee bar - sinks outside bathrooms.

name: Blue Bottle Coffee
directions: To the right in the back

name: Bellingham Technical College - campus center
directions: Second floor of the CC (campus center) building. Around the corner from the main bathrooms.

name: Piccadilly Artisan Creamery
directions: It's in the back. Just ask where the bathroom is and there's a sign.

name: CCM Champlain College
directions: Available on 2nd, 3rd, and 4th floors near gendered restrooms

name: Bellingham Technical College - campus center
directions: Second floor of the CC (campus center) building. Around the corner from the main bathrooms.

name: Foege Hall North 4th floor
directions: Take the stairs from the main entrance to the 4th floor. Make two lefts and walk the corridor until you see a gender-neutral bathroom on your left
comment: Not available on weekends and federal holidays when the University is closed.

name: Panhandle Ear, Nose, and Throat
directions: Enter through the north entrance, office is third down on left side, Suite 140.
comment: The restrooms for the building are not gender neutral! This restroom is in the lobby for an office in the building, but you do not have to be a patient to use it.

name: Here Apartments/ Café Social
directions: between the front desk and the café, on the left
comment: no one cares if you live here or not, or if you buy anything or not!!

name: Kingsgate
directions: Towards the back of kingsgate. Next to the apple shop, there are double doors that lead through onto a corridor, through another set of double doors there are toilets
comment: Toilets are accessible through radar key only. You can purchase one cheaply on amazon

name: The light
directions: Top floor of The Light. Follow directions to disabled toilet.
comment: Toilet is only accessible by radar key. You can purchase one on amazon for about £4. Come in handy for a lot of disabled toilets. Great for a safe place!!!

name: Bunker Hill Community College
directions: Only available in G-Building, near the gymnasium.

name: Arby's
directions: Right side of the store

name: Arby's
directions: Right side of the store

name: House of Fraser
directions: Top floor of house of Fraser, located opposite the cafe.

name: Wayward Lamb
comment: This is a LGBT bar - opens in the late afternoon. I'm sure if you tell them you need a safe bathroom, they will welcome you with open arms

name: HERE Apartments/Café Social
directions: left of the main desk, between the cafe and the desk, towards the mailboxes
comment: lobby only opens for non-residents certain hrs, but you can get in through the café even without buying anything

name: Public Library of Brookline
directions: Our single room, gender neutral restroom is in the Administration Office, upstairs on the second floor.  From the elevator, go straight and then to the door on the right. If you need the restroom when the Administration Office is closed (like in the evening), please just ask any staff member and we will be happy to open the restroom for you.
comment: As a public library, we serve all. Please don't hesitate to ask to use the restroom upstairs if it makes you the most comfortable. Right now this is our only single room restroom available to the public, so we want to make sure people know it is available if needed.

name: Howard County Library Elkridge Express Branch
directions: Two unisex single stall bathrooms on either side of black couch. Location is inside a trailer right inside the driveway for Elkridge Landing Elementary School.
comment: Location is temporary; it will be closed when the main branch re-opens in spring of 2018.

name: The Lowbrow
directions: To the left behind/ near the booths
comment: The host will probably let you use the restroom if you're not a paying customer

name: Pacific Centre
directions: Bottom floor in the hallway by the LUSH Cosmetics
comment: It's a 'family room' with ample space and a baby change table. Only a sitting toilet no urinal

name: Peace Lutheran Church
directions: Education Building Lobby
comment: Single Occupancy, Gender Neutral Restrooms are in the Education Building lobby. Building is open from 9 am to 1 pm Monday through Friday (except school holidays) and Sunday morning from 8:30 to about 12:30. (Someone in the Church Building Office will be happy to open up the Education Building or ensure safe use of the gender specific restrooms in the Church Building during Church Office hours Tuesday through Friday from 10 am to 3 pm, too.)

name: Whole Foods
directions: Back behind dining area, near cashiers.
comment: Technically for customers? But have never seen anyone enforce the rule.

name: Wartburg Chapel
directions: Basement of the chapel, go down the stairs and the restrooms will be to your left
comment: Almost no one uses these restrooms and they're very large, perfect for wheelchairs etc...

name: The Pinto Coffe & Comida
directions: It's easy to find, if you enter through the back by the parking lot it's right by the door.

name: DeRosa University Center
directions: First floor in a hallway across from the ballroom

name: Two Fishermen Grill
comment: Must be paying customer

name: Rockaway Townsquare Mall Food Court
directions: Near the outside entrance to the food court, around the corner from the Gyro place, there is a single family bathroom.

name: Bachmann Fine Arts Center
directions: There are two single stall restrooms in the basement/bottom floor
